Title: Object: Walcot's Roman Compositions
Description: Collector's edition portfolio of 15 individually mounted photogravures after etchings by William Walcot, showing imagined scenes in ancient Rome, Egypt, and Greece. Photogravures
Dimensions: Height: 385 millimetres (size of each mounted sheet)
Curator's comments: The prints are accompanied by a small booklet, "The Walcot Roman Compositions" (Technical Journals Ltd., Tothill St., Westminster), which explains pricing of the whole set at 10 guineas. Single plates could be had for 1 Guinea, or framed in 0.5 inch Ebony or Mahogany at £1. 11. 6 each.
